Class ClassResourceNotFoundException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.io.IOException
          • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.exception.ClassResourceNotFoundException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @FullyTested
public class ClassResourceNotFoundException
extends IOException
    This is a more specific version of FileNotFoundException for resources available via Class.getResourceAsStream(String).
    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
    See Also:
    PathArgs.checkClassResourceAsStreamExists(Class, String, String), Serialized Form

      • ClassResourceNotFoundException

        public ClassResourceNotFoundException(Class<?> classForResource,
                              String resourceName,
                              String message,
                              Throwable optCause)
        Constructs a new ClassResourceNotFoundException object. These should be thrown instead of IOException in cases where the error is specifically class resource path-related.
        Parameters:
        classForResource -
        • class used when check if resource exists
        • Access via getClassForResource()
        resourceName -
        • path to class resource
        • Access via getResourceName()
        • See PathArgs.checkClassResourceAsStreamExists(Class, String, String) for a detailed explanation about resource paths
        message -
        • human-readable error message that is passed directly to superclass constructor
        • Access via Throwable.getMessage()
        optCause -
        • optional underlying cause of this exception that is passed directory to superclass constructor
        • May be null
        • Access via Throwable.getCause()
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if classForResource, resourceName, or message is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if message is empty
